Dominant Values Alert

Indicates that most values in a variable are in the same category, which can limit its contribution to the analysis.

Actions to Consider

Consider updating this variable in the dataset with a more even distribution of data values. Alternatively, consider removing the variable from the model.

Detection Methodology

Einstein Discovery raises this data alert for a variable when one value occurs 90% of the time (the value has a relative frequency of 0.9 or higher).
title: Dominant Values Alert in Einstein Discovery
